    body: 'A CRM for a UK luxury-car dealer that inverts the usual workflow. Drop in a screenshot, photo or WhatsApp message of a vehicle and AdaptiveCRM extracts the details and ranks which customers in the database actually want it — in under ten seconds.',
    href: '/work/adaptive-crm',
    img: '/case-studies/adaptive-crm/slider/avs-04-matches-list.webp',
    alt: 'AdaptiveCRM workspace',
  },
  {
    num: '05',
    title: 'Astra Design System',
    tags: ['SALESFORCE', 'SLDS2', 'TOKEN-FIRST', 'DESIGN SYSTEM'],
    body: 'A token-first design system that closed the gap between SLDS2-aligned Figma designs and their Salesforce implementation — ending the drift between what was designed and what shipped. One source of truth flowing SLDS2 → Astra → Figma → Storybook → VS Code.',
    href: '/work/astra',
    img: '/case-studies/astra/slider/01.webp',
    alt: 'Astra Design System — tokens and components',
  },
  {
    num: '06',
    title: 'Coincover',
    tags: ['CRYPTO SECURITY', 'DESIGN SYSTEM', 'TOKEN-FIRST', 'FINTECH'],
    body: 'A crypto wallet protection and recovery platform serving four audiences at once — customers, partners, admins and operations teams. Built a fully tokenised design system from zero, one component library spanning all four, and shaped the in-house design team into a practice that kept extending it after handover.',
    href: '/work/coincover',
    img: '/case-studies/coincover/slider/01.png',
    alt: 'Coincover wallet recovery flow',
  },
  {
    num: '07',
    title: 'Polaris',
    tags: ['MORTGAGE CALCULATORS', 'BRIDGING & BTL', 'SPECIALIST LENDING'],
    body: 'A standalone mortgage calculator platform built for MFS — production-ready bridging and buy-to-let calculators that run outside Salesforce yet stay embeddable inside it via Visualforce. Built to regain delivery control after a Salesforce-native build stalled.',
    href: '/work/polaris-calculator-suite',
    img: '/case-studies/polaris-calculator-suite/slider/01.webp',
    alt: 'Polaris enterprise pricing board',
  },
  {
    num: '08',
    title: 'Jamf ETP',
    tags: ['DESIGN SYSTEM', 'SECURITY CONSOLE', 'ENTERPRISE'],
    body: "Absorbed a newly acquired mobile threat defence platform into Jamf's design system — a high-stakes security console redesigned, with new patterns contributed back into the broader system.",
    href: '/work/jamf-etp',
    img: '/case-studies/jamf-etp/slider/01.webp',
    alt: 'Jamf ETP security console',
  },
  {
    num: '09',
    title: 'CWT',
    tags: ['DATA VIZ', 'DASHBOARDS', 'DESIGN SYSTEM', 'ENTERPRISE ANALYTICS'],
    body: "Led UX for CWT's Data & Analytics function — internal dashboards across five data domains, and a tokenised analytics design system built from zero for a team new to data viz.",
    href: '/work/cwt',
    img: '/case-studies/cwt/slider/01.webp',
    alt: 'CWT analytics dashboard',
  },
];

const featureCase = cases[0];
const gridCases = cases.slice(1);

interface Step {
  num: string;
  chevron: string;
  title: string;
  body: string;
  pct: string;
  dash: string;
}

const steps: Step[] = [
  {
    num: '01 / Discover',
    chevron: '‹',
    title: 'Understand the problem space',
    body: "Sit with the team and the users. Map constraints, workflows, the messy reality. This phase doesn't accelerate — understanding the problem space takes the time it takes. AI can summarize transcripts and pull patterns from research notes, but the conversations themselves happen at human speed, where the real signal actually lives.",
    pct: '20%',
    dash: '19 100',
  },
  {
    num: '02 / Define',
    chevron: '›',
    title: 'Frame the right problem, not symptoms',
    body: "Synthesise what research actually says, not what everyone assumed it would say. Kill scope that doesn't serve the core job. Sometimes this is a three-week reframe (CheckRR's lending journey, where research surfaced a different core job than the brief assumed). Sometimes the brief is already sharp and Define compresses to a week.",
    pct: '20%',
    dash: '19 100',
  },
  {
    num: '03 / Develop',
    chevron: '‹',
    title: 'Figma to production, via MCP',
    body: 'I design in Figma — components, tokens, layouts, flows. Claude reads the Figma file via MCP and generates production-ready React code. No screenshots, no manual handoff, no fidelity loss. The design file becomes the source of truth. Engineers refine working components, not translating mockups. Develop is where AI compounds hardest.',
    pct: '35%',
    dash: '34 100',
  },
  {
    num: '04 / Deliver',
    chevron: '›',
    title: 'Stay close to launch',
    body: "Pair with engineers through QA, polish the details that Claude missed, then watch it in the wild. AI doesn't ship products. People do. The handoff still requires judgement calls — what's MVP, what's polish, what breaks if we cut it. The gap between design file and shipped product is smaller, but the last 10% still needs a human.",
    pct: '25%',
    dash: '24 100',
  },
];

